				\begin{document}$$\frac{{{\mathrm{Var}}\left( {{\mathrm{E}}\left( {\theta |{\mathrm{chip}}\,{\mathrm{data}}} \right)} \right)}}{{{\mathrm{Var}}(\theta )}},$$\end{document}VarEθ∣chipdataVar(θ),where θ is the haplotype allele count. Var(E(θ | chip data)) was estimated by the observed variance of the allele imputations and Var(θ) was estimated by p(1-p), where p is the allele frequency. This metric has the property of being 0 when the imputation is completely uninformative (the same value is always imputed) and 1 when the imputation is fully informative. Asymptotically, the expectation of the metric equals the r2 between the imputed alleles and the true genotypes.
